RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 1 7F Dirt CR: 60. Maiden Claiming Purse 16600. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BLUE TWIRLIN exchanged light contact with Missing A Sock leaving the gate then stalked from the three path, took the nod toward the half mile pole and kept the edge from that point, raced clear past the five sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn near the rail and was kept alert in the stretch. PLANET FROLIC saved ground, started a bid past the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the three path on the far turn then dug in to clear second later yards. THE MONEY MACHINE stalked inside on the first turn, bid leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn then flattened stride the final sixteenth. MISSING A SOCK exchanged light contact with Blue Twirlin leaving the gate, closed to the front at the three quarter pole and showed the way, was met approaching the half mile pole, gave chase from that point but dropped back leaving the five sixteenths and faded at the rail on the far turn. NELLY TOO rounded the opening turn about the three path, gave chase from the three eighths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn then flattened in the lane. EMBRACEABLE showed little response through the backstretch. SECRET MOMENT raced in the three path the first turn then faded through the backstretch.

ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped break,rated pace inside,met 1/2,chased,faded rail turn

ENTRY.NAME: Blue Twirlin
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped break,stalked 3p,up near 1/2,rail turn,kept sharp lane

ENTRY.NAME: Planet Frolic
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground,bid past 7/16,3p far turn,cleared 2nd later yards

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 2 7F Dirt CR: 58. Claiming Purse 7800. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE SEPTEMBER 29, 2022. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since September 29, 2022 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000 (W V A Races Not Considere d In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MISS WILD took the lead nearing the three quarter pole and tapered to the inside to rate the pace, came under pressure approaching the three eighths pole, contested the edge at the rail on the far turn, was met into the lane but dug in determinedly to hold on. MARKETABILITY rounded the opening turn about the three path, picked up the chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole and raced two deep on the far turn, met the winner at even terms entering the stretch and dueled gamely to the finish. LIGHTFOOT MISS saved early ground, picked up the chase approaching the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the four path on the far turn then dueled through the stretch to take third the final strides. HIT A HOMER HONEY raced inside on the first turn, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn at the rail, eased outward into the lane and was outfinished in the duel through the stretch. WOODSONG'S CASTLE rounded the first turn about the three path, gave chase approaching the seven sixteenths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and was outfinished in the duel through the stretch. SO RED THE ROSE saved ground on the first turn, gave chase passing the half mile pole, rounded the far turn off the rail and weakened in the lane. LIFE IN FLASH showed little response. UPSY DAISY DO showed little response. PRETTY SPECTACULAR was not a factor.

ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground,chased 7/16,4p far turn,dueled 3rd final strides

ENTRY.COMMENT: 3p 1st turn,chased 7/16,2d far turn,even terms 1/8,game to wire

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 3 7F Dirt CR: 82. Claiming Purse 13700. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE MARCH 29, 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Since March 29 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, al lowed 2 lbs. RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROCKY DICE settled in the three and four paths into the first turn, gave chase passing the nine sixteenths pole and steadily improved from that point, rounded the far turn in the three path, dug in for the lead later yards and raced clear under the wire. ELVIRUS took over at the three quarter pole and angled to the rail in to the first turn, came under pressure past the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn near the rail and dug in leaving the turn, but was met, and relented in later yards. TOUGH TO TAME settled off the rail on the first turn, picked up the chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced two deep on the far turn, eased outward leaving the turn and dug in to take third under the wire. MYSTIFIED rounded the first turn in the three path, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn then flattened later yards. LOKOYA ROAD saved ground on the first turn, gave chase approaching the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn at the rail then flattened stride nearing mid-stretch. LADDIE LIAM rounded the opening turn in the four path, gave chase leaving the half mile pole, raced in the four path on the far turn and showed little more. CHESAPEAKE CHARLIE rounded the first turn in the three path, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole but weakened in the three path on the far turn. ATTENTIVE was not a factor after saving early ground.

QUEEN CASHMERE chased the early pace inside then eased outward through the stretch while passing rivals. ONE TOUGH ROSE chased, raced in the four path on the turn and showed little in the lane. ALWAYS SOMETHING dueled to a slim lead past the half mile pole and set a pressured pace, was met toward the quarter pole and weakened leaving the turn. GRANDIOSELY pressured the pace and raced at even terms between horses approaching the quarter pole, but weakened leaving the turn.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 5 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 86. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 19600. RACE.FOOTNOTES: NEVER COMPROMISE settled off the rail on the first turn, bid from the seven sixteenths pole and closed to the front in the three path approaching the head of the lane, dueled clear toward mid-stretch and was kept alert the final sixteenth. THEWITCHISGONE stalked off the rail, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole and dueled to a brief lead three wide at the quarter pole, raced off the rail on the far turn, was met into the lane and flattened the final sixteenth. GOLDEN APPEAL rounded the first turn in the three path then eased out into the backstretch, gave chase approaching the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the five path on the far turn and came along to take third later yards. BLUE N GOLD rounded the opening turn about the three path, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the three path on the far turn and showed little further. NIGHT TRAIN WAYNE raced in the four path the first turn, picked up the chase from the seven sixteenths pole, came through the far turn about the three path and flattened in the lane. MISSIONSNINETYNINE rated a slim lead inside, came under pressure approaching the three eighths pole, was met at the quarter, rounded the far turn off the rail and weakened. RUN TO DAYLIGHT showed little response through the backstretch. AUBURN MILL stalked inside, challenged toward the three eighths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and weakened.

ENTRY.NAME: Blue N Gold

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 6 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 58. Maiden Special Weight Purse 26500. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GREY BOUQUET became a bit fractious in the post parade then set a pressured pace and drew clear toward the five sixteenths pole, contested the turn at the rail and dug in determinedly to eke out the nod over the game stretch challenge of KARMA BUS, who gave chase through the backstretch, contested at a close disadvantage in the three path on the turn and dueled gamely to the finish. CALYPSO JOHN gave chase inside, entered the turn at the rail, was eased to the three path through the turn and dueled in the stretch for third. ESPRESSO chased through the backstretch, rounded the turn near the rail and was outfinished in the stretch duel for third. DIMELO PAPI pressured the early pace, dropped back toward the five sixteenths pole, rounded the turn at the rail and flattened in the lane. ARYA CHARMING chased through the backstretch, raced close off the rail on the turn then flattened in the lane. MAGICAL SURPRISE gave chase through the backstretch and flattened in the three path on the turn. THEIRREGISTRDIMNOT gave chased and rounded the turn off the rail. DON'T GET CAUGHTUP was not a factor. GOLDEN ASSET gave chase and rounded the turn about the four path.

ENTRY.NAME: Karma Bus
ENTRY.OWNER: Brown Nicole and Brown Ronney W

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Henry Mercer Memorial S. CHARLES TOWN RACE 7 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 75. Stakes Purse 75000. FOR REGISTERED ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA BRED TWO YEAR OLDS. $50 nominations close Wednesday, September 13, 2023. $50 to enter with a purse of $75,000 Added. Entries close Wednesday, September 20, 2023 by the usual time of closing. The added monies and al l fees to be divided 60% to the winner, 20% to second, 11% to third, 6% to fourth, and 3% to fifth. Weight: 120 lbs. Field will be limited to ten starters with up to four alternates. Preference to those horses having accumulated the highest career earni ngs at the time of closing of entries. Trophy to the winning owner.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KING KONTIE took the lead leaving the chute and rated the early pace, came under pressure approaching the quarter pole, raced at the rail on the turn, dug in under steady stretch handling but was met at even terms under the wire. JUBAWITHATWIST chased, raced off the rail on the turn and dug in under steady handling to reach the co-winner under the wire. RAN OUT OF TRAINER lacked early speed but steadily improved, raced at the rail on the turn and finished evenly to take third later yards. GRANDY chased, rounded the turn about the three path then flattened stride inside the sixteenth pole. TWO BRONZE STARS gave close early chase inside, rounded the turn near the rail and flattened in the lane. KRISTINACHRYSALIS gave chase, raced at the rail on the turn and showed little in the lane. POWERED BY LOVE gave chase and rounded the turn in the three and four paths. LOVE IS WICKED was not a factor. DORADO chased outside, rounded the turn about the five path and weakened.
